abel":"mentions"},{"source":"recIU5zQctTzB8PO7","target":"recjNRR60PAuFtjha","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recIU5zQctTzB8PO7","target":"recXmfE7tECVVSN23","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recTujePA8J0AVFIo","ref":"Heb.7.1","text":"For this Melchisedec, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him;","year":64},{"id":"recBljAlHkPf77Wez","ref":"Heb.7.2","text":"To whom also Abraham gave a tenth part of all; first being by interpretation King of righteousness, and after that also King of Salem, which is, King of peace;","year":64},{"id":"recKKax2BbNDqrLUZ","ref":"Heb.7.3","text":"Without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning of days, nor end of life; but made like unto the Son of God; abideth a priest continually.","year":64},{"id":"recb1zHOXvEGiPm8h","ref":"Heb.7.4","text":"Now consider how great this man was, unto whom even the patriarch Abraham gave the tenth of the spoils.","year":64},{"id":"recCdJo84WKnNaczF","ref":"Heb.7.5","text":"And verily they that are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a commandment to take tithes of the people according to the law, that is, of their brethren, though they come out of the loins of Abraham:","year":64},{"id":"recR4JkacYnDJClpQ","ref":"Heb.7.6","text":"But he whose descent is not counted from them received tithes of Abraham, and blessed him that had the promises.","year":64},{"id":"rec6KL8f2bPwUzFdC","ref":"Heb.7.7","text":"And without all contradiction the less is blessed of the better.","year":64},{"id":"recJA0RkA78YUEzem","ref":"Heb.7.8","text":"And here men that die receive tithes; but there he receiveth them, of whom it is witnessed that he liveth.","year":64}]}
